  "prompt": "I'm going through a midlife crisis at 18. What should I do?",
  "response": "At 18, you're experiencing typical young adult anxieties, not a true midlife crisis. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Mental health support\n- Talk to a counselor or therapist\n- Share feelings with trusted friends/family\n- Consider your emotions are normal for this age\n\n2. Self-exploration\n- Try different activities and hobbies\n- Set short and long-term goals\n- Focus on personal growth\n- Explore potential career paths\n\n3. Personal development\n- Continue education\n- Learn new skills\n- Travel if possible\n- Build self-confidence\n- Practice self-care\n\n4. Social connections\n- Maintain healthy relationships\n- Meet new people\n- Join clubs or groups\n- Network professionally\n\n5. Practical steps\n- Create a realistic life plan\n- Start saving money\n- Build professional skills\n- Stay open to opportunities\n\n6. Perspective\n- Understand that feeling uncertain is normal\n- You have many years ahead\n- Embrace personal growth\n- Don't be too hard on yourself\n\nThese feelings are common and don't define your entire life. Focus on personal development and remain positive about your future.\n\nWould you like to discuss any specific concerns you're experiencing?",
